description.plain: Jake Hagood, better known as Who Is Fancy, is an American singer. He co-signed with Scooter Braun and Scott Borchetta on Big Machine Label Group and Dr. Luke on Prescription Songs. His single “Goodbye” was released in early 2015, peaking at number 29 on the Billboard Mainstream Top 40 chart.

description.plain:
Like his first single “Goodbye”, Who Is Fancy’s new single “Boys Like You” is a relatively simple love song. However, also like “Goodbye”, it transcends the barriers of sexual orientation. Fancy himself is openly gay, while both Ariana Grande and Meghan Trainor are straight, so this song could be identifiable for people who are gay, straight, or anything in between.

It was released on November 23, 2015. The music video shows animated forms of all three artists chasing after a ripped pool boy.

songs.title: Goodbye

description.plain:
“Goodbye” is the debut single from enigmatic (at the time) artist Who Is Fancy.

It seems like a simple breakup song on the surface, but Fancy brushes on nonbinary expression, dishonesty about one’s true feelings, and how heartbreak (and the moving-on process) transcends all sexualities.



Three music videos were made, each with a different actor lip-syncing. Each one shows the main actor being turned from themselves into a more presentable but faker version of themselves for the sake of the video-within-the-video.

The videos can be watched here, here, and here.
